 rest-frame UV luminosities, are flatter since they\noverpredict/underpredict SFRs for low/high star forming objects and yield\ndeviations from the intrinsic relation from 0.10 dex to -0.13 dex at $z \\sim\n4$. We suggest that the severe tension between different observational studies\ncan be broadly explained by the fact that different groups employ different\ntechniques to infer their SFRs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Jan 2020 19:01:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-29"}
