{"id":"2001.07703","submitter":"Farrukh Mukhamedov M.","authors":"Farrukh Mukhamedov, Ahmed Al-Rawashdeh","title":"Generalized Dobrushin Ergodicity Coefficient and Ergodicities of\n  Non-homogeneous Markov Chains","comments":"29 pages. arXiv admin note: text overlap with arXiv:2001.06266","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.FA math.DS math.OA math.PR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In our earlier paper, a generalized Dobrushin ergodicity coefficient of\nMarkov operators (acting on abstract state spaces) with respect to a projection\n$P$, has been introduced and studied. It turned out that the introduced\ncoefficient was more effective than the usual ergodicity coefficient. In the\npresent work, by means of a left consistent Markov projections and the\ngeneralized Dobrushin's ergodicity coefficient, we investigate uniform and weak\n$P$-ergodicities of non-homogeneous discrete Markov chains (NDMC) on abstract\nstate spaces. It is easy to show that uniform $P$-ergodicity implies a weak\none, but in general the reverse is not true. Therefore, some conditions are\nprovided together with weak $P$-ergodicity of NDMC which imply its uniform\n$P$-ergodicity. Furthermore, necessary and sufficient conditions are found by\nmeans of the Doeblin's condition for the weak $P$-ergodicity of NDMC. The weak\n$P$-ergodicity is also investigated in terms of perturbations. Several\nperturbative results are obtained which allow us to produce nontrivial examples\nof uniform and weak $P$-ergodic NDMC. Moreover, some category results are also\nobtained. We stress that all obtained results have potential applications in\nthe classical and non-commutative probabilities.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Jan 2020 12:42:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-22"}
